<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1258] Delete temporary data directory after unit test finishes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1258</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today in unit testsuite most of the time when a test case is setup a temporary directory will be created with a random int as suffix, and will not be deleted after the test. After a few unit tests this will create tons of directories in java.io.tmpdir (/tmp for Linux). Would be better to remove them for clean unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12694579">KAFKA-1258</key>
            <summary>Delete temporary data directory after unit test finishes</summary>
