                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13898307" author="jkreps" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2014 21:00:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah this annoys me too. The core problem is that java provides File.deleteOnExit but this doesn&apos;t work for directories. Instead what we should do is change TestUtils.createTempDir to add a shutdown hook that deletes the directory recursively.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13898861" author="sriramsub" created="Wed, 12 Feb 2014 06:43:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Look into &lt;a href=&quot;http://junit.org/javadoc/4.9/org/junit/rules/TemporaryFolder.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://junit.org/javadoc/4.9/org/junit/rules/TemporaryFolder.html&lt;/a&gt;. Helps to manage temp folders in junit. It may be supported only in java 7. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14059741" author="omkreddy" created="Sat, 12 Jul 2014 10:38:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/23439/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/23439/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch origin/trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14059742" author="omkreddy" created="Sat, 12 Jul 2014 10:46:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Junit 4.7 can be used to manage temporary folders. But this  requires&lt;br/&gt;
changes in all the test cases and some base test classes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Submitted patch by adding shutdown hook to TestUtils.tempDir method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14059897" author="jkreps" created="Sat, 12 Jul 2014 19:50:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
